<p>I am new in JavaFx and don't know some things, f.e. how to bind collections of type A, which contains collections of type B to TreeView. F.e. I have model classes:</p>  <pre><code>class A {     private final StringProperty name = new SimpleStringProperty();     private SetProperty&lt;B&gt; objects = new SimpleSetProperty();      // setters &amp; getters }  class B {     private final StringProperty title = new SimpleStringProperty();     private SetProperty&lt;C&gt; objects = new SimpleSetProperty();      // setters &amp; getters }  class C {     private final IntegerProperty title = new SimpleIntegerProperty();      // setters &amp; getters } </code></pre>  <p>How can I display objects of these classes in TreeView in next way?</p>  <ul> <li>obj_A1  <ul> <li>obj_B1.1</li> <li>obj_B1.2  <ul> <li>obj_C1.1</li> </ul></li> <li>obj_B1.3</li> </ul></li> <li>obj_A2  <ul> <li>obj_B2.1</li> <li>obj_B2.3</li> </ul></li> </ul>  <p>Does TreeView has any property which I can bind my collection of  types on?</p>